--#Arkana#

--1.13 Segment of a list
--- Define the segment function such that (segment m n xs) is the list of the elements of xs between positions m and n. For example.
----- segment 3 4 [3, 4, 1, 2, 7, 9, 0] == [1,2]
----- segment 3 5 [3, 4, 1, 2, 7, 9, 0] == [1,2,7]
----- segment 5 3 [3, 4, 1, 2, 7, 9, 0] == []

--1.13 Segmento de una lista
---Definir la funcion segmento tal que (segmento m n xs) es la lista de los elementos de xs comprendidos entre las posiciones m y n. Por ejemplo.
-----segmento 3 4 [3, 4, 1, 2, 7, 9, 0] == [1,2]
-----segmento 3 5 [3, 4, 1, 2, 7, 9, 0] == [1,2,7]
-----segmento 5 3 [3, 4, 1, 2, 7, 9, 0] == []
